text: Sophia Kleinherne (born 12 April 2000) is a German footballer who plays as a defender for Eintracht Frankfurt and the Germany national team. ==Career== Kleinherne made her international debut for Germany on 9 November 2019 in a friendly match against England, which finished as a 2–1 win. ==Career statistics== ===International=== {| class="wikitable" style="text- align:center" |- !colspan=3|Germany |- !Year!!Apps!!Goals |- |2019||1||0 |- |2020||2||0 |- !Total!!3!!0 |} ==Notes== ==References== ==External links== * * * * Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:People from Warendorf (district) Category:Footballers from North Rhine-Westphalia Category:German women's footballers Category:Germany women's youth international footballers Category:Germany women's international footballers Category:Women's association football defenders Category:FSV Gütersloh 2009 players Category:1.
